               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-145-person1266">
                  ROBERT 
                  HOGARD
               <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1266" type="surname" value="HOGARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1266" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1266" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18240603-145-viclabel780" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-145-victim1265 t18240603-145-viclabel780"></join>, and live in Waterloo-place; I left my gig in <placeName id="t18240603-145-crimeloc781">Goswell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-145-crimeloc781" type="placeName" value="Goswell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-145-crimeloc781" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-145-off778 t18240603-145-crimeloc781"></join> on Saturday morning, the 1st of May, in the care of a boy in the employment of Mr. Budd. I was gone into the house, and had left my coat in it; I came out in about a quarter of an hour, and it was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-145-person1267">
                  HENRY 
                  GREEN
               <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1267" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1267" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1267" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had the care of Mr. Hogard's chaise. I was at the horses head; there was a brown great-coat and a blue cloak in the chaise. I was looking towards Goswell-street, and the chaise was towards Old-street, when the coat was stolen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-145-person1268">
                  JOHN 
                  TWEEDY
               <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1268" type="surname" value="TWEEDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1268" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1268" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On the 1st of May, about ten or eleven o'clock, I saw the prisoner just turning round Old-street, rolling up this coat, and running fast; I followed him, and Bradford caught him. It was about fifty yards from Mr. Budd's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-145-person1269">
                  THOMAS 
                  BRADFORD
               <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1269" type="surname" value="BRADFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1269" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-145-person1269" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I followed the prisoner, who was running. I stopped him, and took the coat from him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 18.</p>
